hopobject.body: History fosamax generic price walmart These are the same crucial individuals that in a natural system would live long, full lives, protecting their mates and cubs and contributing their genes to future generations.Despite the wild claims that trophy hunting brings millions of dollars in revenue to local people in otherwise poor communities, there is no proof of this.Even pro-hunting organisations like the International Council for Game and Wildlife Conservation have reported that only three percent of revenue from trophy hunting ever makes it to the communities affected by hunting.The rest goes to national governments or foreign-based outfitters.The money that does come into Africa from hunting pales in comparison to the billions and billions generated from tourists who come just to watch wildlife. If lions and other animals continue to disappear from Africa, this vital source of income - nonconsumptive tourism - will end, adversely impacting people all over Africa.
